Enroll Caller in Voice ID

If your admin enabled Voice ID for your org, you can enroll callers in Voice ID who agree to use their voice to authenticate themselves. Voice ID appears only when you're on a call.

This feature is available with these telephony models: 
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

To view Voice ID, open the Voice Call record page or Omni-Channel widget. Click Enroll Caller to enroll the caller.

Voice ID evaluates the caller’s voice to authenticate them and determine their fraud risk level. To evaluate the caller’s voice, click Evaluate Voice. If a caller wants to opt out of Voice ID, click Opt Out.
title: Enrolling Callers in Voice ID with Service Cloud
